WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:00:09.950 --> 00:00:11.160
What a shame!

3
00:00:11.160 --> 00:00:13.370
I win again!

4
00:00:14.740 --> 00:00:16.500
You guys have a lot of free time.

5
00:00:16.870 --> 00:00:18.870
Hand over the cell keys.

6
00:00:18.870 --> 00:00:20.040
Huh?

7
00:00:21.750 --> 00:00:23.380
Who the hell are you?

8
00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:28.720
Hey.

9
00:00:39.980 --> 00:00:43.020
Who said you imbeciles could speak?

10
00:00:42.860 --> 00:00:45.070
"Ghost Princess" Perona
Hollow-Hollow Fruit

11
00:00:45.440 --> 00:00:47.030
What'd you say?!

12
00:00:47.030 --> 00:00:49.900
You've got some nerve, missy.

13
00:00:51.410 --> 00:00:55.080
Maybe a simple "Shut up"
is easier to understand?

14
00:01:00.750 --> 00:01:02.920
Kneel before me.

15
00:01:02.920 --> 00:01:05.090
Negative...

16
00:01:05.090 --> 00:01:06.340
Hollow!

17
00:01:06.340 --> 00:01:09.550
Negative! Negative!

18
00:01:09.550 --> 00:01:12.590
Negative! Negative!

19
00:01:22.060 --> 00:01:24.980
I'm sorry that I'm more cowardly
than a water flea...

20
00:01:24.980 --> 00:01:28.570
I wanna give up piracy
and live out my days in prison...

21
00:01:36.240 --> 00:01:38.120
Alright, we're set!

22
00:01:38.120 --> 00:01:40.000
Let's go, guys.

23
00:01:59.680 --> 00:02:02.190
Not very lively around here...

24
00:02:06.020 --> 00:02:07.400
Hey! You!

25
00:02:07.900 --> 00:02:08.520
Huh?

26
00:02:19.370 --> 00:02:22.120
Ouch. Ow, ow, ow...

27
00:02:22.120 --> 00:02:23.500
Hey, you.

28
00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:24.670
Huh?

29
00:02:30.250 --> 00:02:31.340
You're...

30
00:02:33.680 --> 00:02:37.300
Are you the one they call Koby the Hero?!

31
00:02:36.840 --> 00:02:39.260
Captain Koby
Marine Headquarters
(SWORD)

32
00:02:39.260 --> 00:02:45.560
I'll free you, so you're going to
free Master Moria from his cell.

33
00:02:46.560 --> 00:02:47.520
Moria?

34
00:02:53.440 --> 00:02:55.450
Gecko Moria is here?

35
00:02:55.820 --> 00:02:57.200
Yes, he is!

36
00:02:57.200 --> 00:02:59.660
Master Moria's life is at risk!

37
00:03:04.830 --> 00:03:06.290
Free him...?

38
00:04:37.050 --> 00:04:41.430
The Legendary Hero

39
00:04:42.010 --> 00:04:43.220
Big news!

40
00:04:43.220 --> 00:04:47.100
Beehive, the Pirate Island
New World

41
00:04:43.550 --> 00:04:45.890
Captain Koby has escaped!

42
00:04:45.890 --> 00:04:47.100
Seriously?!

43
00:04:49.810 --> 00:04:52.940
He escaped, so he's not
the commodore's prize anymore, right?!

44
00:04:52.940 --> 00:04:55.530
How much will we get if we capture him?!

45
00:04:57.280 --> 00:05:00.990
Well, we don't need to put a bounty on him!

46
00:05:00.990 --> 00:05:03.490
Cross Guild will pay it for us!

47
00:05:03.490 --> 00:05:06.370
I bought odds on him with a win ticket!

48
00:05:06.370 --> 00:05:08.330
The payout's gonna be big!

49
00:05:08.330 --> 00:05:10.330
How much will we get if we kill him?!

50
00:05:10.960 --> 00:05:12.630
Wait till you hear this!

51
00:05:14.590 --> 00:05:16.750
He's a five-star bounty!

52
00:05:16.750 --> 00:05:20.420
That means five treasure chests!
A total of 500 million berries!

53
00:05:20.420 --> 00:05:23.050
A five-star bounty?!

54
00:05:23.050 --> 00:05:25.260
Captains are usually only worth one!

55
00:05:28.100 --> 00:05:31.100
Alright! Let's hit the jackpot!

56
00:05:31.100 --> 00:05:33.980
Let the hunt begin!

57
00:05:36.270 --> 00:05:39.320
I'm feeline a tickle on
the left side of my chest.

58
00:05:39.650 --> 00:05:42.950
That's where the slaves are
held before they're sold...

59
00:05:48.660 --> 00:05:51.250
Are they breaking out?!

60
00:05:51.580 --> 00:05:53.750
The slaves escaped?!

61
00:05:54.580 --> 00:05:56.960
Can we hunt them, Pizarro?!

62
00:05:56.960 --> 00:05:58.590
Don't be stupid!

63
00:05:58.590 --> 00:06:00.420
You guys are so greedy!

64
00:06:00.970 --> 00:06:02.680
Bring them all back!

65
00:06:02.680 --> 00:06:04.140
Don't even kill Koby...

66
00:06:04.590 --> 00:06:06.220
or I'll tell Teach!

67
00:06:08.560 --> 00:06:11.020
Why is that mountain talking...?

68
00:06:11.390 --> 00:06:13.520
He knows that we're here!

69
00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:14.730
Let's hurry!

70
00:06:17.730 --> 00:06:18.690
What?

71
00:06:19.820 --> 00:06:21.650
This is it for us...

72
00:06:22.110 --> 00:06:26.660
Just run away before we slow you down.

73
00:06:26.660 --> 00:06:28.870
Don't give up hope.

74
00:06:28.870 --> 00:06:31.250
I'll lure them all away...

75
00:06:31.750 --> 00:06:35.880
so make sure everyone escapes!

76
00:06:35.880 --> 00:06:36.630
Well then...

77
00:06:37.630 --> 00:06:39.210
We'll meet again!

78
00:06:41.130 --> 00:06:42.760
Thanks!

79
00:06:45.010 --> 00:06:47.220
Thank you, Captain Koby...

80
00:06:50.260 --> 00:06:52.600
You're a saint!

81
00:06:57.560 --> 00:07:00.480
Shiryu of the Rain
Clear-Clear Fruit
Invisible Man

82
00:07:00.480 --> 00:07:05.070
You should have captured
them yourself, Pizarro.

83
00:07:09.200 --> 00:07:12.410
Like I said, Teach would be pissed.

84
00:07:11.870 --> 00:07:15.410
"Corrupt King" Avalo Pizarro
Isle-Isle Fruit
Island Man

85
00:07:15.410 --> 00:07:19.040
I just break things whenever I meowve.

86
00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:19.880
Huh?

87
00:07:23.260 --> 00:07:25.800
Mind if I take a shot?

88
00:07:25.800 --> 00:07:29.010
Vasco Shot... What are mew gonna do?

89
00:07:35.230 --> 00:07:38.980
They can't run if I burn down the town.

90
00:07:38.520 --> 00:07:42.070
"Heavy Drinker" Vasco Shot
Glug-Glug Fruit
Booze Man

91
00:07:49.660 --> 00:07:52.990
Hey, don't do that!
That would be a meowssive fire!

92
00:07:53.330 --> 00:07:55.450
Teach would be furrious!

93
00:07:55.450 --> 00:07:58.210
It's fine. Leave it to me.

94
00:07:58.710 --> 00:08:03.300
Furget it! We just finished
fixing up Rocky Port!

95
00:08:03.800 --> 00:08:07.170
Would you rather leave it to Wolf?

96
00:08:11.430 --> 00:08:12.760
Wolf?

97
00:08:12.760 --> 00:08:16.980
"Colossal Battleship" Sanjuan Wolf
Huge-Huge Fruit
Gigantification Man

98
00:08:14.640 --> 00:08:16.980
That's meowt of the question!

99
00:08:16.980 --> 00:08:19.980
Mew might as well just
destroy the whole town!

100
00:08:24.610 --> 00:08:25.690
I found him!

101
00:08:31.490 --> 00:08:33.700
Damn! I guess I can't outrun them!

102
00:08:36.200 --> 00:08:37.160
Somehow...

103
00:08:38.210 --> 00:08:43.500
I have to keep them busy until
everyone can escape to the sea!

104
00:08:45.880 --> 00:08:47.880
Koby the Hero!

105
00:08:51.800 --> 00:08:56.640
Koby the Hero, I want to turn this island...

106
00:08:58.100 --> 00:09:00.940
this Pirate Island...

107
00:09:01.310 --> 00:09:05.150
into a full-fledged nation!

108
00:09:05.150 --> 00:09:09.360
A World Government-affiliated nation!

109
00:09:10.610 --> 00:09:12.320
It'll be the Blackbeard Kingdom...

110
00:09:12.660 --> 00:09:14.700
with me as its king!

111
00:09:18.160 --> 00:09:20.120
How's that?

112
00:09:20.120 --> 00:09:22.210
Stop this nonsense.

113
00:09:22.580 --> 00:09:24.710
There's no way it would work!

114
00:09:25.130 --> 00:09:27.170
It'd be a country of criminals!

115
00:09:27.550 --> 00:09:31.550
Hey, don't step on a man's dream!

116
00:09:31.550 --> 00:09:35.550
I'll negotiate with them
using you as a bargaining chip.

117
00:09:36.850 --> 00:09:40.600
If the government or the Marines
give in to terrorists, we're all doomed!

118
00:09:41.440 --> 00:09:43.940
Anyway, you're wasting your time.

119
00:09:44.810 --> 00:09:45.860
Because...

120
00:09:46.570 --> 00:09:48.530
I'm a member of SWORD!

121
00:09:49.780 --> 00:09:51.610
SWORD?

122
00:09:51.610 --> 00:09:53.320
What the hell is that?

123
00:09:53.320 --> 00:09:54.870
Oh, I see...

124
00:09:54.870 --> 00:09:55.570
Huh?

125
00:09:55.570 --> 00:09:57.580
This isn't gonna go well.

126
00:09:57.580 --> 00:09:59.910
Give up on the trade, Teach.

127
00:10:07.590 --> 00:10:09.130
What he means...

128
00:10:09.130 --> 00:10:12.170
is that he's a Marine but also not.

129
00:10:13.470 --> 00:10:15.930
He gave up his Marine code.

130
00:10:18.140 --> 00:10:22.690
SWORD is a group of Marines that have
already submitted their resignations.

131
00:10:23.100 --> 00:10:27.270
Which means they could even fight
the Four Emperors without permission.

132
00:10:27.270 --> 00:10:31.610
They can operate however they choose
and disregard any and all orders.

133
00:10:31.610 --> 00:10:32.820
They're free agents.

134
00:10:33.320 --> 00:10:34.820
In exchange...

135
00:10:36.030 --> 00:10:39.870
the Marines are in no way
responsible for their actions...

136
00:10:40.490 --> 00:10:42.620
and can fire them anytime.

137
00:10:45.210 --> 00:10:46.580
I see!

138
00:10:47.080 --> 00:10:50.840
So there's the normal idiots who
sit around waiting for permission,

139
00:10:51.260 --> 00:10:54.680
and you guys, who charge in
without thinking twice!

140
00:10:57.140 --> 00:10:59.810
Now that I get it, I like your style!

141
00:11:01.100 --> 00:11:02.140
But...

142
00:11:02.140 --> 00:11:04.770
I'm not gonna change the plan!

143
00:11:05.350 --> 00:11:07.150
I'll do it anyway!

144
00:11:08.360 --> 00:11:10.570
Even if you're in SWORD,

145
00:11:11.280 --> 00:11:14.820
the people still call you a hero.

146
00:11:14.820 --> 00:11:18.240
I wonder if the Marines can
really afford to just abandon you.

147
00:11:19.030 --> 00:11:21.490
Let's ask the public, shall we?!

148
00:11:22.620 --> 00:11:25.660
That way the government can't just
wash their hands of this!

149
00:11:29.040 --> 00:11:31.750
Until then, lock him up!

150
00:11:33.170 --> 00:11:35.010
I can't wait!

151
00:11:35.010 --> 00:11:37.720
Don't let him escape!

152
00:11:39.470 --> 00:11:42.310
Get back here, Koby!

153
00:11:48.480 --> 00:11:49.360
Hey!

154
00:11:49.360 --> 00:11:55.650
I'll free you, so you're going to
free Master Moria from his cell.

155
00:11:56.240 --> 00:11:58.450
I may have cooperated with a pirate...

156
00:11:58.950 --> 00:12:01.330
but you gotta do what you gotta do!

157
00:12:08.870 --> 00:12:09.790
What's that?

158
00:12:19.470 --> 00:12:22.180
Three Marines spotted at the port!

159
00:12:22.680 --> 00:12:25.220
What? Marines?! No way!

160
00:12:25.850 --> 00:12:27.180
Hurry up!

161
00:12:28.230 --> 00:12:30.810
They're strong! Be careful!

162
00:12:32.610 --> 00:12:34.730
Did someone come to rescue me?

163
00:12:34.730 --> 00:12:36.070
No, no!

164
00:12:36.070 --> 00:12:37.740
How arrogant of me!

165
00:12:37.740 --> 00:12:38.950
I'm ashamed!

166
00:12:58.630 --> 00:12:59.760
Who are they?!

167
00:12:59.760 --> 00:13:01.260
Why are they so strong?!

168
00:13:01.260 --> 00:13:03.760
They're heading toward
the center of the town!

169
00:13:03.760 --> 00:13:04.720
What do they want?!

170
00:13:04.720 --> 00:13:07.140
Who cares?! Stop them!

171
00:13:14.730 --> 00:13:15.730
What?

172
00:13:15.730 --> 00:13:17.190
Guns don't work on them!

173
00:13:18.650 --> 00:13:20.990
That's as far as you go!

174
00:13:24.410 --> 00:13:25.990
He cut his head off!

175
00:13:30.500 --> 00:13:32.210
I took one down!

176
00:13:32.540 --> 00:13:33.920
That'll teach you!

177
00:13:40.510 --> 00:13:41.800
That hurt...

178
00:13:41.800 --> 00:13:42.800
What?!

179
00:13:42.800 --> 00:13:43.930
A logia?!

180
00:13:44.260 --> 00:13:45.800
What's with this guy?!

181
00:13:45.800 --> 00:13:48.100
It's like he's made of clay!

182
00:13:49.640 --> 00:13:52.020
Where are you, Koby?!

183
00:13:54.230 --> 00:13:55.980
H-Hey...

184
00:13:56.360 --> 00:13:58.730
Are those buildings moving?!

185
00:13:58.730 --> 00:14:00.490
No, stupid! Of course not!

186
00:14:00.490 --> 00:14:02.450
You drink too much!

187
00:14:09.790 --> 00:14:12.250
Go on! Be a good little boy!

188
00:14:15.380 --> 00:14:17.130
Get a move on!

189
00:14:17.130 --> 00:14:20.090
What a weird lady. Who is that?

190
00:14:20.090 --> 00:14:22.880
Come on, straighten up!

191
00:14:25.180 --> 00:14:27.510
You look pathetic!

192
00:14:27.510 --> 00:14:29.640
Come on! Come on! Come on!

193
00:14:29.640 --> 00:14:32.140
She's whipping a building...

194
00:14:33.350 --> 00:14:35.560
What is it? Staring, are we?

195
00:14:35.560 --> 00:14:37.270
What? No, I...

196
00:14:37.820 --> 00:14:39.980
S-She's a Marine?!

197
00:14:46.740 --> 00:14:50.410
Is it that rare for a pirate
to set eyes on a Marine?

